Last year April, the country was hit with the devastating news that Churchill Show comedian Ayeiya had passed away.Â He died after his car hit a pole near the Catholic University of Eastern Africa on Magadi Road. His fellow comedian DJ Shiti has taken to social media to pen down an emotional letter to Ayeiya, crediting him for his great work and inspiring many. He wrote: "Today is Exactly One year since you went to dine with the Angels... you set the pace for us in the Comedy Industry.... Most of us Started our career replicating your reputation.... from comparison jokes to story Jokes... as well as real life situation jokes.... I know you are still with us... True soldiers Never Die... Ayeiyaaaaa....poapoa..."   